In rejecting the application , Judge James Allsop said Australia does not have a legal right to stop whaling in international waters protected by Australia because Japan does not recognize Australia 's jurisdiction there . 
`` Whaling is also part of the Japanese culture , '' he said . 
The next year it resumed catches under a loophole that allows `` research whaling , '' despite international protests . 
Japan announced in April it plans to seek permission to extend its research whaling program in the Antarctic when the IWC meets later this month . 